# Implementation Plan - Listening, Reading, Writing, Speaking, and IELTS Exam System

This plan outlines the architecture and implementation details for the Prepme IELTS exam system. It supports five exam types (LISTENING, READING, WRITING, SPEAKING, and IELTS full test), section-based test structures (passages, audio sections, speaking cue cards, etc.), question-level configurations (Multiple Choice, True/False/Not Given, Matching Headings, etc.), auto-scoring for receptive skills, draft/final submissions, and practice history with analytics.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> - **Test/Exam Entity Hierarchy**: We will introduce a self-referencing relationship on `TestEntity`. When a test represents an `IELTS` full exam, it acts as a container pointing to its 4 child tests (Listening, Reading, Writing, Speaking). This avoids duplicate structures and allows clean modular practice or full mock testing.
> - **Omission of Answer Keys during Practice**: When fetching test details via `/api/exams/{id}`, correct answers and explanations will be withheld from students to prevent client-side cheating. They are only disclosed after submission or when fetching completed practice history.
> - **Auto-scoring for Receptive Skills**: Auto-scoring maps correct answer counts to standard IELTS Band Scores (0.0 to 9.0) using pre-defined academic mapping grids for Listening and Reading.
> - **Speaking Audio Upload**: The front-end will upload Speaking recordings using the existing `/api/upload` endpoint, then pass the uploaded Cloudinary URL when submitting the practice.

---

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Enums
We will add two new enums to represent the type of exam and the specific types of questions.

#### [NEW] [ExamType.java](file:///d:/prepme/project-website_prepme/BE/WEBSITE_PREPME/src/main/java/com/fpt/website_prepme/enums/ExamType.java)
- `LISTENING`, `READING`, `WRITING`, `SPEAKING`, `IELTS`

#### [NEW] [QuestionType.java](file:///d:/prepme/project-website_prepme/BE/WEBSITE_PREPME/src/main/java/com/fpt/website_prepme/enums/QuestionType.java)
- `TRUE_FALSE_NOT_GIVEN`, `MATCHING_HEADINGS`, `MULTIPLE_CHOICE`, `FILL_IN_THE_BLANK`, `SHORT_ANSWER`

---

### 2. Database Entities

#### [NEW] [TestEntity.java](file:///d:/prepme/project-website_prepme/BE/WEBSITE_PREPME/src/main/java/com/fpt/website_prepme/model/entity/TestEntity.java)
Holds general metadata for an exam or a single skill test.
- `title` (String, nullable = false)
- `examType` (ExamType, enum, nullable = false)
- `duration` (Integer) - allocated time in seconds
- `audioUrl` (String, length = 512) - audio file for Listening (or skill subtest)
- `description` (TEXT)
- `parentTest` (ManyToOne -> TestEntity, nullable) - Reference to IELTS package if this is a subtest
- `childTests` (OneToMany -> TestEntity) - Subtests of an IELTS package
- `sections` (OneToMany -> TestSectionEntity) - Sections/Passages in this test

#### [NEW] [TestSectionEntity.java](file:///d:/prepme/project-website_prepme/BE/WEBSITE_PREPME/src/main/java/com/fpt/website_prepme/model/entity/TestSectionEntity.java)
Divides the test into structural parts.
- `test` (ManyToOne -> TestEntity, nullable = false)
- `sectionNumber` (Integer, nullable = false) - e.g. 1, 2, 3, 4
- `title` (String) - e.g. "Passage 1", "Cue Card Topic"
- `passage` (TEXT) - HTML content for Reading passages or instructions
- `cueCard` (TEXT) - Prompt details for Speaking cue cards
- `audioUrl` (String, length = 512) - Optional section-specific audio URL
- `questions` (OneToMany -> TestQuestionEntity)

#### [NEW] [TestQuestionEntity.java](file:///d:/prepme/project-website_prepme/BE/WEBSITE_PREPME/src/main/java/com/fpt/website_prepme/model/entity/TestQuestionEntity.java)
Stores question details.
- `section` (ManyToOne -> TestSectionEntity, nullable = false)
- `questionNumber` (Integer, nullable = false) - 1 to 40
- `questionType` (QuestionType, enum, nullable = false)
- `questionText` (TEXT)
- `options` (TEXT) - JSON string containing choices (e.g. `["A. Choice 1", "B. Choice 2"]`)
- `correctAnswer` (String) - Answer key for auto-checking
- `explanation` (TEXT) - Rationale for the answer

#### [MODIFY] [PracticeHistoryEntity.java](file:///d:/prepme/project-website_prepme/BE/WEBSITE_PREPME/src/main/java/com/fpt/website_prepme/model/entity/PracticeHistoryEntity.java)
- Add a nullable reference: `test` (ManyToOne -> `TestEntity`) to trace the history directly to its exam source.

