### 3. Data Transfer Objects (DTOs)

#### [NEW] [TestListDTO.java](file:///d:/prepme/project-website_prepme/BE/WEBSITE_PREPME/src/main/java/com/fpt/website_prepme/model/dto/TestListDTO.java)
List view metadata. Includes ID, title, type, duration, section count, and created timestamp.

#### [NEW] [TestDetailDTO.java](file:///d:/prepme/project-website_prepme/BE/WEBSITE_PREPME/src/main/java/com/fpt/website_prepme/model/dto/TestDetailDTO.java)
Complete structure including sections and questions (optionally masking `correctAnswer` depending on request context). Supports composite `IELTS` exams by nesting child tests.

#### [NEW] [TestSectionDTO.java](file:///d:/prepme/project-website_prepme/BE/WEBSITE_PREPME/src/main/java/com/fpt/website_prepme/model/dto/TestSectionDTO.java)
Metadata, passage, cueCard, and questions inside a section.

#### [NEW] [TestQuestionDTO.java](file:///d:/prepme/project-website_prepme/BE/WEBSITE_PREPME/src/main/java/com/fpt/website_prepme/model/dto/TestQuestionDTO.java)
Individual questions (hides answer key when used in the exam viewer).

#### [NEW] [TestSubmitRequest.java](file:///d:/prepme/project-website_prepme/BE/WEBSITE_PREPME/src/main/java/com/fpt/website_prepme/model/dto/TestSubmitRequest.java)
- `answers` (Map<Long, String> - Maps questionId/questionNumber to user answer string)
- `submissionContent` (String - Essay contents for Writing, or transcript for Speaking)
- `recordingUrl` (String - Audio recording URL for Speaking)
- `completionTime` (Integer - duration in seconds)
- `status` (PracticeStatus - DRAFT or COMPLETED)

#### [NEW] [PracticeHistoryDTO.java](file:///d:/prepme/project-website_prepme/BE/WEBSITE_PREPME/src/main/java/com/fpt/website_prepme/model/dto/PracticeHistoryDTO.java)
Response for a completed practice run, including answers, correct answers, auto-score results, and AI feedback.

#### [NEW] [PracticeStatisticsDTO.java](file:///d:/prepme/project-website_prepme/BE/WEBSITE_PREPME/src/main/java/com/fpt/website_prepme/model/dto/PracticeStatisticsDTO.java)
Aggregated practice count, average score, and calendar frequencies for charts.

---

### 4. Repositories
- `TestRepository`: standard paging and filtering by `ExamType`.
- `TestSectionRepository`: standard CRUD.
- `TestQuestionRepository`: standard CRUD.
- `PracticeHistoryRepository`: Query methods for fetching history by current user, status, skill type, and statistics aggregates.

---

### 5. Services & Utilities

#### [NEW] [IeltsScoringUtils.java](file:///d:/prepme/project-website_prepme/BE/WEBSITE_PREPME/src/main/java/com/fpt/website_prepme/utils/IeltsScoringUtils.java)
Stateless utility to map raw correct answers (0 - 40) into official Academic IELTS Band Scores (0.0 - 9.0) for LISTENING and READING.

#### [NEW] [TestService.java](file:///d:/prepme/project-website_prepme/BE/WEBSITE_PREPME/src/main/java/com/fpt/website_prepme/service/TestService.java)
Declares methods:
- Get list of exams (paginated, filtered by `ExamType`).
- Get exam details by ID (with answers stripped for practice mode).
- Submit test responses (scoring, history mapping).
- Get practice histories and detailed reviews.
- Get practice dashboard statistics.
- Seed demo exams (mock data loader helper).

#### [NEW] [TestServiceImpl.java](file:///d:/prepme/project-website_prepme/BE/WEBSITE_PREPME/src/main/java/com/fpt/website_prepme/service/impl/TestServiceImpl.java)
Implementation details:
- Validates the exam and user context.
- For Listening/Reading: Iterates through submitted answers, matches them against `correctAnswer`, determines correct count, maps to IELTS band score using `IeltsScoringUtils`, and saves to `PracticeHistoryEntity` with `status = COMPLETED`.
- For Writing: Saves user submission text, word counts, and tracks time. Allows drafts.
- For Speaking: Saves speaking recording audio URL and optional transcripts.
- For IELTS (Composite): Combines score results or generates practice history entries.

---

### 6. Controllers

#### [NEW] [TestController.java](file:///d:/prepme/project-website_prepme/BE/WEBSITE_PREPME/src/main/java/com/fpt/website_prepme/controller/TestController.java)
Exposes endpoint paths:
- `GET /api/exams` - List tests (pages, filters, keyword searches).
- `GET /api/exams/{id}` - Details of the exam (answers hidden).
- `POST /api/exams/{id}/submit` - Submit practice answers.
- `POST /api/exams/seed` - Optional admin/dev helper to seed standard mock exams.

#### [NEW] [PracticeHistoryController.java](file:///d:/prepme/project-website_prepme/BE/WEBSITE_PREPME/src/main/java/com/fpt/website_prepme/controller/PracticeHistoryController.java)
Exposes endpoint paths:
- `GET /api/practice-histories` - Get history of practice logs.
- `GET /api/practice-histories/{id}` - Detailed review of a past practice, showing answers, correct markers, and keys.
- `GET /api/practice-histories/statistics` - Practice frequency, average bands, and weekly completion metrics.

---

## Verification Plan

### Automated Compilation Check
We will build the codebase using Gradle:
```bash
./gradlew compileJava
```

### Manual API Tests
We will seed mock exams and perform endpoint testing (using curl or Postman equivalent check) to ensure correct responses:
1. Verify `GET /api/exams` returns the list of tests (including Listening, Reading, Writing, Speaking, and IELTS).
2. Verify `GET /api/exams/{id}` returns correct sections and questions without leaking the `correctAnswer`.
3. Verify submission of Listening/Reading exams automatically checks answers, awards correct scores, and computes IELTS band scores.
4. Verify Writing draft saving and submittal records the written text.
5. Verify Speaking submissions accept a recording URL and save appropriately.
6. Verify practice history reviews retrieve complete details (with answer keys) and statistics reports function correctly.
